      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.807646">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Samba Badlock Critical Vulnerability</name>
        <family>General</family>
        <cvss_base>7.5</cvss_base>
        <severities score="7.5">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2019-09-27T17:17:00Z</date>
            <score>7.5</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Samba is prone to badlock vulnerability.|insight=Multiple flaws exist due to:

  - multiple errors in DCE-RPC code

  - a spoofing Vulnerability in NETLOGON

  - the LDAP implementation did not enforce integrity protection for LDAP connections

  - the SSL/TLS certificates are not validated in certain connections

  - not enforcing Server Message Block (SMB) signing for clients using the SMB1 protocol

  - an integrity protection for IPC traffic is not enabled by default

  - the MS-SAMR and MS-LSAD protocol implementations mishandle DCERPC connections

  - an error in the implementation of NTLMSSP authentication|affected=Samba versions 3.0.x through 4.4.1.

  NOTE: Samba versions 4.2.11, 4.3.8 are not affected|impact=Successful exploitation of this vulnerability
  leads to Man-in-the-middle (MITM) attacks, to causes denial of service, to spoof
  and to obtain sensitive session information.|solution=Upgrade to samba version 4.2.11, or 4.3.8,
  or 4.4.2, or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Upgrade to samba version 4.2.11, or 4.3.8,
  or 4.4.2, or later.</solution>
