        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N|summary=PostgreSQL is prone to multiple information disclosure
  vulnerabilities.|insight=Multiple flaws are due to:

  - Some selectivity estimation functions did not check user privileges before
    providing information from pg_statistic, possibly leaking information.

  - An error in 'pg_user_mappings' view.|affected=PostgreSQL version before 9.2.21, 9.3.x
  before 9.3.17, 9.4.x before 9.4.12, 9.5.x before 9.5.7, and 9.6.x before 9.6.3.|impact=Successful exploitation will allow an
  unprivileged attacker to steal some information.|solution=Upgrade to PostgreSQL version 9.2.21 or
  9.3.17 or 9.4.12 or 9.5.7 or 9.6.3 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Upgrade to PostgreSQL version 9.2.21 or
  9.3.17 or 9.4.12 or 9.5.7 or 9.6.3 or later.</solution>
        <refs>
