        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H|summary=Oracle MySQL is prone to a denial of service (DoS) vulnerability.|insight=Multiple errors exist as,

  - In sql-common/client.c script 'mysql_prune_stmt_list' function, the for loop
    adds elements to pruned_list without removing it from the existing list.

  - If application gets disconnected just before it tries to prepare a new
    statement, 'mysql_prune_stmt_list' tries to detach all previously prepared
    statements.|affected=Oracle MySQL version before 5.6.21 and
  5.7.x before 5.7.5 on Linux|impact=Successful exploitation of this vulnerability
  will allow attackers to cause crash of applications using that MySQL client.|solution=Upgrade to Oracle MySQL version 5.6.21 or
  5.7.5 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
