        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=Insufficient symlink verification could allow data access
  outside share path.|insight=All versions of Samba from 3.0.0 to 4.3.2 inclusive are vulnerable to
  a bug in symlink verification, which under certain circumstances could
  allow client access to files outside the exported share path.

  If a Samba share is configured with a path that shares a common path
  prefix with another directory on the file system, the smbd daemon may
  allow the client to follow a symlink pointing to a file or directory
  in that other directory, even if the share parameter 'wide links' is
  set to 'no' (the default).|affected=Samba versions 3.0.0 through 4.1.21, 4.2.0 through 4.2.6 and
  4.3.0 through 4.3.2.|impact=|solution=Update to version 4.1.22, 4.2.7, 4.3.3 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 4.1.22, 4.2.7, 4.3.3 or later.</solution>
