        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:A/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:L/A:N|summary=Samba is prone to a memory information leak vulnerability.|insight=A server memory information leak bug over SMB1
  if a client can write data to a share. Some SMB1 write requests were not correctly
  range checked to ensure the client had sent enough data to fulfill the write.|affected=Samba versions before 4.4.16,
  4.5.0 before 4.5.14, and 4.6.0 before 4.6.8.|impact=Successful exploitation will allow a client with
