        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:N|summary=PostgreSQL is prone to an authorization check vulnerability.|insight=|affected=PostgreSQL versions prior to 9.4.26, 9.5.x prior to 9.5.21, 9.6.x prior to
  9.6.17, 10.x prior to 10.12, 11.x prior to 11.7 and 12.x prior to 12.2.|impact=The ALTER ... DEPENDS ON EXTENSION sub-commands do not perform authorization
  checks, which can allow an unprivileged user to drop any function, procedure, materialized view, index, or
  trigger under certain conditions. This attack is possible if an administrator has installed an extension and an
  unprivileged user can CREATE, or an extension owner either executes DROP EXTENSION predictably or can be
  convinced to execute DROP EXTENSION.|solution=Update to version 9.4.26, 9.5.21, 9.6.17, 10.12, 11.7, 12.2 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
