  'ZEND_CONCAT()', and 'ZEND_ASSIGN_CONCAT()' opcodes, and the 'ArrayObject::uasort' method, trigger
  memory corruption by causing a userspace interruption of an internal function or handler.|affected=PHP versions 5.2.x through 5.2.13 and 5.3.x through 5.3.2.|impact=Successful exploitation could allow local attackers to bypass
  certain security restrictions and to obtain sensitive information.|solution=Update to version 5.2.14, 5.3.3 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
