        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:N/A:N|summary=This host is prone to an information disclosure vulnerability.|insight=The flaw is due to the block cipher padding not being deterministic and not covered by the Message Authentication Code|affected=|impact=Successful exploitation will allow a  man-in-the-middle attackers gain access to the plain text data stream.|solution=Possible Mitigations are:

  - Disable SSLv3

  - Disable cipher suites supporting CBC cipher modes

  - Enable TLS_FALLBACK_SCSV if the service is providing TLSv1.0+|vuldetect=Evaluate previous collected information about this service.|solution_type=Mitigation</tags>
        <solution type="Mitigation">Possible Mitigations are:

  - Disable SSLv3

  - Disable cipher suites supporting CBC cipher modes

  - Enable TLS_FALLBACK_SCSV if the service is providing TLSv1.0+</solution>
